channel.title: My run isn't working
channel.description:
Hey I'm having trouble with my run and it's not running which is really frustrating me. I am using the source complexityrsps and I need someone to tell me the right code for the run here is my code. When ever I try to run it says The system cannot find the path specified Press any key to continue...
@echo off title Project Insanity "C:\Program Files\Java\jdk1.7.0_45\bin\java.exe" -cp bin;deps/poi.jar;deps/mysql.jar;deps/mina.jar;deps/slf4j.jar;deps/slf4j-nop.jar;deps/jython.jar;log4j-1.2.15.jar;-server -XX:+AggressiveHeap -XX:MaxHeapFreeRatio=90 -XX:MinHeapFreeRatio=90 -XX:+DisableExplicitGC -XX:+RelaxAccessControlCheck -XX:+UseParallelGC -XX:CompileThreshold=1 -XX:ThreadStackSize=128 server.Server pause

item.title: My run isn't working
item.dc:creator: @sspoke sspoke
item.description:
@sspoke wrote:

Put this

C:\Program Files\Java\jdk1.7.0_45\bin\

inside any folder’s address bar on your computer and see that it actually goes there, if it doesn’t go there… then go into

C:\Program Files\

and find the Java folder if you can’t find it then install java SDK

try also

C:\Program Files (x86)

it could also install into that folder it’s really based on what kind of computer you got.
